Sentencas: Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-delta-BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-delta (SDC-BZCY), one of the promising electrolytes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs), often suffers from its high sintering temperature.
Titulo: Improved sintering behavior and electrical performance of Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ - BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-δ (SDC -BZCY) composite electrolytes with the addition of iron (III) oxide for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: In this study, SDC-BZC (weight ratio 50:50) electrolytes with addition of x wt.% Fe2O3 (x = 0, 0.5, 1.0, 1.5 and 2.0), named as SDC-BZCY-xFe, were fabricated.
Titulo: Improved sintering behavior and electrical performance of Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ - BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-δ (SDC -BZCY) composite electrolytes with the addition of iron (III) oxide for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The effect of Fe(2)O(3 )addition on sintering and electrical properties were investigated.
Titulo: Improved sintering behavior and electrical performance of Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ - BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-δ (SDC -BZCY) composite electrolytes with the addition of iron (III) oxide for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The results show that Fe2O3 makes the sintering temperature of SDC-BZCY effectively decrease from 1500 degrees C to 1400 degrees C.
Titulo: Improved sintering behavior and electrical performance of Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ - BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-δ (SDC -BZCY) composite electrolytes with the addition of iron (III) oxide for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The SDC-BZCY-1.5Fe electrolyte achieves the highest conductivity of 8.06 x 10(-3) S cm(-1) at 700 degrees C, times higher than that of pure SDC-BZCY (1.78 x 10(-3) S cm(-1)).
Titulo: Improved sintering behavior and electrical performance of Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ - BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-δ (SDC -BZCY) composite electrolytes with the addition of iron (III) oxide for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: With humidified hydrogen (20 ml min(-1)) as the, fuel and static air (40 ml min(-1)) as the oxidant, the SDC-BZCY-1.5Fe electrolyte-supported single cell show much higher OCV values (0.87 Vat 600 degrees C, 0.85 Vat 700 degrees C, 0.80 Vat 800 degrees C) than pure SDC, and obtain the peal power density of 133 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Improved sintering behavior and electrical performance of Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-δ - BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-δ (SDC -BZCY) composite electrolytes with the addition of iron (III) oxide for IT-SOFCs
